### Description

I was asking a large language model to help me optimize providers for Angular.

It hallucinated the following syntax:
````ts
@NgModule({
  imports: [
    // other imports ...
    // lazy-load the date picker intl and date adapter modules
    () => import('./date-picker-intl.module').then(m => m.DatePickerIntlModule),
    () => import('./date-adapter.module').then(m => m.DateAdapterModule),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {
````

I know that's not a thing. But could we make it a thing? It's a really elegant syntax to lazy load modules which need to provide lazily provide dependencies to 'root', but you don't need to do for the first paint of the app.

### Proposed solution

Make async imports a valid type in the imports[] array, not just the module / component

### Alternatives considered

Loading things via Router

